@accepts(gdouble, gdouble)
@returns(none)
def set_bounds(angle_start, angle_end)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Sets the initial and final angles of a rotation behaviour; angles &gt;= 360
degrees get clamped to the canonical interval &lt;0, 360).</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>angle_start :</p></td>
<td><p>initial angle in degrees, between 0 and 360.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>angle_end :</p></td>
<td><p>final angle in degrees, between 0 and 360.</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 0.4</p>
